properties.Name: PolicyholderSuitableProduct
properties.Description:
One of more Product(s) that have been judged to be suitable for marketing to the associated Policyholder for the period indicated.

For example, a family with small children is targeted for school lunch products via promotions, advertising etc. whereby a retired couple would not.

Columns.Name: PolicyholderId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Policyholder.

Columns.Name: ProductId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Product.

Columns.Name: PeriodStartDate
Columns.Description: The period start date for which the associated Product(s) are identified as suitable for the associated Policyholder.

Columns.Name: PeriodEndDate
Columns.Description: The period end date for which the associated Product(s) are identified as suitable for the associated Policyholder.

Columns.Name: ProductSuitabilityNote
Columns.Description: Notes, comments or additional information regarding the Product suitability for the associated Policyholder.

Columns.Name: ProductSuitabilityRatingId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Product Suitability Rating.
